      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/West_Hempstead%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The town’s name evolved from “West of Hempstead” after the LIRR built a station west of Hempstead in 1891; the name stuck.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        14
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Local source"
      ],
      "source": "local"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The West Hempstead Public Library opened in 1956 and was chartered by the state in 1967.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/West_Hempstead%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Halls Pond Park, the main park, was dedicated by Nassau County in 1961.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        15
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/West_Hempstead%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "The George Washington School, originally Carl Street School, was authorized by voters in 1929 for $355,000.",
